•	Data Security & Privacy: Ensuring the system meets healthcare data regulations (like HIPAA) and securing patient records using encryption and blockchain technology.
•	Scalability: Handling large volumes of data, including medical records, appointments, and billing without performance degradation.
•	Integration with Existing Systems: Many hospitals use legacy systems that may not be easy to integrate with a modern HMS.
•	Interoperability: Ensuring compatibility with other healthcare systems and ensuring smooth data exchange between labs, pharmacies, and hospitals.
•	Blockchain Adoption: Educating users about the Health Data Incentive Program and the use of blockchain for secure and incentivized data sharing.

